The paper deals with the optimization of power grids with renewable energy sources, specifically wind energy. This falls under the category of control systems (cs.SY) as the paper discusses methods for controlling the transmission grids. The paper also uses optimization techniques and models, which are common in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and distributed computing (cs.DC). The paper also mentions the use of second-order cone programming, which is a common technique in electrical engineering and power systems (cs.ET). Finally, the paper deals with the optimization of power grids, which is a topic in network engineering (cs.NE).
